The Iris flower classification dataset comprises 150 samples of Iris flowers, categorized into three species:Â¶
Iris setosa
Iris versicolor
Iris virginica
The data set contains 3 classes of 50 instances each, where each class refers to a type of iris plant.One class is linearly separable from the other 2; the latter are NOT linearly separable from each other.
Attribute Information:

Sepal length in cm
Sepal width in cm
Petal length in cm
Petal width in cm
Class
The dataset is widely used as a benchmark in machine learning for supervised classification tasks aiming to accurately classify Iris flowers based on their measurements.

